-- U.S. municipal bond market continued to shrink in Q1 -Fed
-- 
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 12:04PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, June 5 (Reuters) - The amount of outstanding U.S. municipal bonds continued shrinking in the first quarter to $3.661 trillion from $3.671 trillion in the final quarter of 2013, Federal Reserve data released on Thursday showed.

Households, the backbone of the market, held $1.604 trillion bonds in the first quarter, compared to $1.626 trillion the quarter before and $1.676 trillion in the first quarter of 2013.